data.text:
This is a list of the oldest living people in the world. Supercentenarians that are categorized as "validated" have had their ages authenticated by an organization that specializes in age validation, such as the Gerontology Research Group (GRG), the Guinness World Records (GWR) or International Database on Longevity (IDL).

Supercentenarians that are categorized as "pending validation" have their ages partially authenticated, but remain to be fully processed by an age validation organization. The last group, "unvalidated", refers to supercentenarians that have not had their ages authenticated but for whom there is sufficient reliable-source reporting to at least have a claimed date of birth. However, only claimants age 110114 that could potentially be validated in the future are included here, although exaggerated claims 115-129 can be found at Living longevity claims, and those false claims above 130 can be found at Living longevity myths.

Since the death of 117-year-old Maria Branyas Morera of Spain on 19 August 2024, Tomiko Itooka (born 23 May 1908) of Japan is the oldest living person whose age is validated.

Since the death of 112-year-old Shi Ping of China on 29 June 2024, John Tinniswood (born 26 August 1912) of the United Kingdom is the oldest living man whose age is validated.

See also: Oldest living men

Bold names indicates the individual is believed to be the oldest known living resident of their country.
